# Trivy ignore list for known transitive CVEs we cannot fix in this repo.
# Each entry explains the constraint source and removal criteria. Delete
# entries as soon as the upstream pin is relaxed and the dependency is
# picked up through uv.lock.

# cryptography is pinned by f2 (Douyin SDK) at 44.0.0. Fixed in 46.0.5.
# Remove once f2 publishes a release that allows cryptography >= 46.0.5
# or we replace the transitive dependency.
CVE-2026-26007

# protobuf is pinned by f2 at 5.28.3. Fixed in 5.29.5 / 5.29.6 / 6.31.1.
# Remove once f2 relaxes the constraint or a compatible release lands in
# uv.lock.
CVE-2025-4565
CVE-2026-0994

# ``uv sync --frozen --no-dev`` under uv 0.11.6 still materializes
# black's dist-info in the runtime image even after we dropped the
# ``[project.optional-dependencies]`` duplicate. The black binary is
# never invoked in production and CVE-2026-32274 requires running
# black against attacker-controlled paths, so there is no reachable
# exploit. Remove this entry after auditing the uv behavior and either
# moving to ``uv export`` + ``pip install`` in the Dockerfile or
# upgrading to a uv release that drops dev metadata under --no-dev.
CVE-2026-32274
